Supreme Court Amendment Rules (No. 2) 2008

21 October 2008

We, the Honourable Ewan Charles Crawford, Chief Justice, the Honourable Pierre William Slicer, the Honourable Peter Ethrington Evans, the Honourable Shan Tennent and the Honourable David James Porter, Puisne Judges of the Supreme Court of Tasmania, on the recommendation of the Rule Committee, make the following Rules of Court under the Supreme Court Civil Procedure Act 1932 .

1. Short title
    These Rules of Court may be cited as the Supreme Court Amendment Rules (No. 2) 2008 .

2. Commencement
    These Rules of Court take effect on the day on which Part 1.2 of Chapter 1 of the Legal Profession Act 2007 commences.

3. Principal Rules
    In these Rules of Court, the Supreme Court Rules 2000 are referred to as the Principal Rules.
